H.B. NO.
C.D. 1
1 The department shall rely on an institution's certification
2 that the employee was provided due process in accordance with
3 this section.
4 (f) Each institution in the State, when requested by
5 another institution, shall share with that institution the
6 existence of any employee investigation that includes
7 allegations of infliction of harm to a student, including
8 ongoing investigations.
9 (g) An institution that provides information or an opinion
10 about an employee's job performance to a prospective employing
11 institution shall be presumed to be acting in good faith and
12 shall have qualified immunity from civil or criminal liability
13 for disclosing the information and for the consequences of the
14 disclosure.
15 (h) The good faith presumption under subsection (g) shall
16 be rebuttable upon a showing, by a preponderance of the
17 evidence, that the information or opinion disclosed was:
18 (1) Knowingly false; or
19 (2) Knowingly misleading.
